East 37th Street, n.s., w. from no. 103, Manhattan
ca. 1902

Gift of Catherine C. (Mrs. Charles D.) Dickey, Chestnut Hill, Philadelphia, Penna., Sept 1971

237 East 37th Street, West side, showing the Murray Hill Vocational #P.S.49.
Board of Education, of N.Y.C.
1920.

E. 37th Street, north side, west of Second Avenue. Adjoining the corner is the Murray Hill Industrial High School. Adjacent to same is the newly erected portion of the New York Telephone Co. building. This replaced two former tenements, No's 229 and 231. At Lexington Avenue appears the rear of the Hotel White. Note the grade, giving this area its long familiar name.

January 8, 1939
